The flood situation in Bangladesh has worsened, with millions displaced and hundreds dead.
Major rivers like the Ganges and Brahmaputra are overflowing, causing widespread devastation.
Evacuations are underway, but the situation remains dire.
The UK has pledged aid to support relief efforts in the affected regions.
As the floodwaters continue to rise, the need for assistance is critical to prevent further loss of life and provide essential supplies to those in need.
The government and international organizations are working together to address this humanitarian crisis.
